30/06/2003
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktas told journalists Sunday (29 June) that Cyprus' EU membership process should be put on hold until a new government, representing both communities on the island, is formed. Denktas also called for resumption of talks on the future of Cyprus but did not comment about preconditions for negotiations.
In related developments, Council of Europe (CoE) Human Rights Commissioner Alvaro Gil Robles met Saturday with leaders of the "Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus" (TRNC). Robles held separate meetings with TRNC Presidential Undersecretary Ergun Olgun and Supreme Court Chairman Taner Erginel. The meetings were part of preparations for the CoE report on human rights. (Anadolu Agency, Anka - 29/06/03)
